title._content: Catalogue of Books, Deseronto Public Library (1896), pp.42-43

description._content:
Pages 42 and 43 of the 1896 catalogue of books in Deseronto Public Library, Deseronto, Ontario, continuing the listing of Class M (Miscellaneous) and with an advertisement for the "Canadian Order of Oddfellows - in connection with the Manchester Unity - Loyal Hastings Lodge No. 158 Meets every 2nd and 4th Wednesday in each Month, McCullough's Hall, St. George Street.
Officers for the year 1895
R. W. Lloyd, N.G.
N. T. Lowe, V.G.
A. D. McIntyre, P.N.G., Sec
D. W. Dart, P.N.G., Treas.
C. W. Tucker, P.N.G., L.M.
G. Morden, R.S.N.G.
J. W. Cannon, L.S.N.G.
S. Russell, R.S.V.G
J. H. Thompson, L.S.V.G
Jesse Thomas, R.S.S.
W. Dean, Warden
H. C. Fowkes, Conductor
J. A. Wilson, I.G.
W. Cook, O.G.
W. D. Perry, P.N.G
Objects of the Society:
The social and moral development of its members.
Assurance at lowest possible cost. Relief during sickness and at death to see remains decently buried and provide for widows and orphans.
Based upon the principles of the Brotherhood of Man and the Fatherhood of God."
